    "body": "Script to reproduce the issue:\r\n```\r\ngmt begin map png\r\ngmt basemap -R0.725/0.825/1/2 -JX10c/1c -BS -Bx0.01\r\ngmt basemap -R0.725/0.825/1/2 -JX10c/1c -BS -Bx0.01+0.005 -Y-h  # WRONG\r\ngmt basemap -R0.725/0.825/1/2 -JX10c/1c -BS -Bx0.01+0.005 --FORMAT_FLOAT_MAP=%.3g -Y-h\r\ngmt basemap -R0.725/0.825/1/2 -JX10c/1c -BS -Bx0.01+0.005 --FORMAT_FLOAT_MAP=%.11g -Y-h\r\ngmt basemap -R0.725/0.825/1/2 -JX10c/1c -BS -Bx0.01+0.005 --FORMAT_FLOAT_MAP=%.12g -Y-h  # WRONG\r\ngmt basemap -R0.725/0.825/1/2 -JX10c/1c -BS -Bx0.01+0.005 --FORMAT_FLOAT_MAP=%.13g -Y-h\r\ngmt end show\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Output image:**\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3974108/115160660-69152080-a067-11eb-8b67-0c5e3070a3b8.png)\r\n\r\nIt seems that when `FORMAT_FLOAT_MAP` is `%.12g` (the default value), the annotations are wrong when phase shift (`+0.005`) is used.",
